<!-- ============== POV ============== -->
<section class="pov">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="pov-grid">
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="t-eyebrow" style="color: var(--ink-300); margin-bottom: 20px;"><span class="dot" style="background: var(--build-400);"></span>Our point of view</div>
        <p class="pov-lede">
          The work is still human.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pov-body reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 120ms;">
        <p>
          The AI rush has flooded organisations with more learning platforms than ever, but their people still can't do the work the organisation needs them to do. Platforms promise learning on demand. <strong>Building real capability takes people</strong> — experts who teach them to apply what they know, give feedback in the moment, and stand by them.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is how people learn to do the work that hasn't been done before: the work that's new, the work that's harder, the work that doesn't have a playbook yet.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's not a training philosophy. It's how we help organisations do the work the future demands.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

